While notable examples have been excavated from the {{ill|Furu Ruins|ja|布留遺跡|12=draft}} in {{ill|Tenri|ja|天理市|12=draft}}, similar haniwa are found in most Kofuns with cylindrical haniwa, ranging from {{ill|Yamagata Prefecture|ja|山形県|12=draft}} and {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|12=draft}} in the east to {{ill|Kagoshima Prefecture|ja|鹿児島県|12=draft}} in the west. At the {{ill|Ishiyama Kofun|ja|石山古墳|12=draft}} in {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|12=draft}}, one morning glory-shaped haniwa was placed for every 4–5 cylindrical haniwa.

